                  <msItem class="assignment of term">
                     <p>
                        <seg type="docType">Assignment of term.</seg>
                        <placeName key="place_116047">Roche Court (Hampshire)</placeName>. <origDate when="1693">5 William and Mary. Jul. 5, 1693</origDate>. Indenture tripartite made between (1) Thomas Legh of Ridge, Cheshire,
                        esq., and Susanna his wife, only daughter of Francis Gregg of Ilkeston,
                        Derbyshire, gent., deceased, and sister and sole administratrix of William
                        Gregg of Ilkeston, Derbyshire, only son of Francis Gregg; (2) Mary Gregg of
                        St Andrew Holborn, Middlesex, widow, Thomas Gregg and Joseph Gregg of
                        Clements Inn, Middlesex, gents., Benjamin Gregg of the Middle Temple,
                        London, gent., and Francis Gregg of Clements Inn, Middlesex, gent, executors
                        of the last will and testament of Thomas Gregg, citizen and Pewterer of
                        London, gent., and (3) Thomas Harris of St Giles in the Fields, Middlesex,
                        gent., and Robert Southam of the Inner Temple, London, gent., reciting a
                        deed dated 1 August 1664 an assignment of a term of years to various parties
                        including Thomas Gregg, deceased, of the messuage known as Roch Court and
                        lands, Hampshire, in trust for Francis Gregg, deceased, and being an
                        assignment by (1) to (3) of the property (endorsed: 'Assignement from Legh
                        &amp; al[iis] to Harris &amp; Southam. 5o July 1693').</p>
